.TH "drm_ioctl" 9 "drm_ioctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_ioctl \- ioctl callback implementation for DRM drivers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" drm_ioctl
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cmd "  ","
.BI "unsigned long arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
file this ioctl is called on
.IP "cmd" 12
ioctl cmd number
.IP "arg" 12
user argument
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Looks up the ioctl function in the DRM core and the driver dispatch table,
stored in \fIdrm_driver.ioctls\fP. It checks for necessary permission by calling
\fBdrm_ioctl_permit\fP, and dispatches to the respective function.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative error code on failure.
